Literature.

34:43.617 --> 34:45.159
Literature saved his life.

34:45.179 --> 34:49.244
And that character, Santiago, is embedded in that guy's heart.

34:49.284 --> 34:50.285
I know it.

34:50.305 --> 34:51.086
That's the connection.

34:51.126 --> 34:52.668
And how recently did this happen?

34:53.509 --> 34:54.911
A couple years ago.

34:55.311 --> 35:00.578
Just remarkable, because it, to me, brought so many things about the program together.

35:00.598 --> 35:05.123
You know, I began to think, this is part of what happens at the best moments.

35:05.693 --> 35:06.494
around the table.

35:07.135 --> 35:08.938
And that's how literature can save life.

35:09.600 --> 35:10.120
And it does.

35:10.341 --> 35:11.543
And it changes guy's life.

35:11.563 --> 35:12.645
It saved his life.

35:12.665 --> 35:13.867
Salvation is there.

35:13.887 --> 35:28.992
The anecdote that Mike Leahy, the probation officer over in Florida, told me about, he, his supervisor came down unexpectedly from Boston one day and said, you know, I'm going with you today.

35:29.213 --> 35:31.296
And this guy who had been through the programs

35:31.580 --> 35:33.162
was on his list of people to see.

35:33.182 --> 35:34.844
So they went to the guy's house.

35:34.864 --> 35:36.186
That was the last call of the day.

35:37.427 --> 35:39.289
And it's a third floor walk up in Florida.

35:39.750 --> 35:42.373
The guy did his thing.

35:42.433 --> 35:43.294
They're all set to leave.

35:43.314 --> 35:45.837
And the guy tugged on Mike's lead.

35:45.857 --> 35:48.160
He says, I want to show you something.

35:48.180 --> 35:52.165
They walk through the mess of his house, the third floor.

35:52.485 --> 35:53.507
They get to the back room.

35:53.667 --> 35:56.811
He opens up a door with all the books.

35:56.831 --> 35:58.553
The guy had bought at yard sale.

35:58.613 --> 36:00.355
He says, I've bred three quarters of them.

36:00.740 --> 36:02.783
and I'm going to read all of them before I'm through.

36:02.923 --> 36:06.128
And Mike said, and that was really good.

36:06.148 --> 36:16.563
He said, but the best part was I saw him after that, and his son was heading down the same path that the father was on.

36:16.583 --> 36:24.054
And when he saw his father turn, he started reading the books his father was reading, and they started talking about them.

36:24.094 --> 36:30.223
And he said, that to me is the quintessential story of changing lines through literature.

36:30.406 --> 36:36.434
I mean, there's a whole family, there's two generations impacted by one court.

36:39.438 --> 36:42.762
It's a story that's echoed in various ways all around.

36:42.802 --> 36:53.876
The human ties we've made, the people we've wanted to respect and like and admire at this table, go way beyond any statistic of recidivism ever created.

36:53.896 --> 36:58.202
It's a matter of trying to translate that to other people.

36:58.553 --> 36:59.875
And that's the problem.

37:00.055 --> 37:01.738
We're asking them to take a chance.

37:01.778 --> 37:05.083
We're asking them to risk their... Does it work?

37:05.203 --> 37:06.886
There's no guarantee with any individual.

37:06.966 --> 37:08.448
Oh, with anything.

37:08.468 --> 37:13.255
And the women have comparable kinds of stories, I'm sure.

37:13.395 --> 37:23.310
And the reading list there is formulated by... Well, it's a very... I think of it as a very grassroots operation, in any case.

37:23.330 --> 37:27.717
So wherever one of these springs up, you know,

37:27.967 --> 37:32.653
facilitate a professor on a campus in whatever district or locality.

37:33.515 --> 37:43.509
It's pretty, I try to give them what advice and what wisdom they might have, but in the end, it's their choice in terms of what books they want to use.

37:43.549 --> 37:47.835
Imagine they're going to be passionate about the books that they want to use.

37:47.895 --> 37:52.381
We have extensive reading lists so they can make those choices that even though they don't have to use.

37:53.302 --> 37:57.568
And the result is that each group really has

37:58.038 --> 38:04.587
different books based apart on the choices that the facilitator wants to make out of their own passion.

38:04.607 --> 38:09.833
And also, again, in terms of the group itself, if it's a women's group, they're going to obviously want to shape it around.

38:09.853 --> 38:10.114
Sure.

38:10.634 --> 38:14.820
If it's an ethnic minority, they'll often think a little, at least, about the mix.

38:15.200 --> 38:26.475
There's a seminar day once or twice a year at a conference center at Northeastern University, and academics and probation officers and judges from around the country will collect that.

38:27.215 --> 38:34.245
And my impression of these people is that they're all highly intellectual, and they're very independent.

38:34.265 --> 38:40.173
They all have their own proud take on how they go about this program.

38:40.613 --> 38:43.678
There is no set series of commands from above.

38:44.118 --> 38:55.534
This is the original table at which the program was created, and yet academics from a wide variety of situations and backgrounds have been able to take this idea

38:56.003 --> 38:58.245
and do something positive with it.

38:58.265 --> 38:59.967
Use it as a template.

38:59.987 --> 39:02.090
And isn't it astonishing that you have it in Texas?

39:02.830 --> 39:03.831
That's the most, to me.

39:04.953 --> 39:07.055
Right in the Bible, though.

39:07.075 --> 39:08.416
It is incredible.

39:08.436 --> 39:09.117
Yeah, it is.

39:09.137 --> 39:10.218
It really is.

39:10.258 --> 39:11.700
I told you that when we were talking before.

39:11.720 --> 39:13.302
Well, I saw it on your website.

39:13.362 --> 39:15.084
Right, look at this.

39:15.144 --> 39:18.707
I remember when those guys came up originally from Texas.

39:18.728 --> 39:20.509
They said, you know, they're interesting.

39:20.529 --> 39:21.911
They wanted to come up.

39:21.931 --> 39:23.833
I kept saying to them,

39:23.982 --> 39:27.645
So, you know, it's one thing to have this program going to Massachusetts for all time.

39:28.086 --> 39:29.888
I think we're going to make a point out of that.

39:29.928 --> 39:31.069
Yeah, because I can see it.

39:31.089 --> 39:34.652
If we can ever get the program going in Texas, that's a whole different world now.

39:34.672 --> 39:46.343
I can just see a lot of my critics saying, look at him, he's got this chapter, Reach Out and Read, Massachusetts Operation, this one, Massachusetts Operation, Eating Out Liberals, that's what he's exploring.

39:46.363 --> 39:50.967
Well, I've got an essay, I think it's up on the web somewhere, it's a short one.

39:51.248 --> 39:53.770
It's published also, it's kind of obvious people.

39:54.037 --> 39:58.884
They had a paragraph about just that kind of thing.

39:59.705 --> 40:04.492
